summary.name: Anscombe's Quartet
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing four sets of data with nearly identical simple descriptive statistics, yet have very different distributions and appear very different when graphed.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the correlation between X and Y in each set and whether there is a linear relationship or not.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the shape of the distribution of Y in each set and whether it is skewed or not.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the overall correlation between X and Y across all sets and whether there is a linear relationship or not.

goals.question: What is the difference in the distribution of Y between set I and set II of Anscombe's Quartet?

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='X', y='Y', hue='Series')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between X and Y in each set of Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', hue='Series', multiple='dodge', shrink=.8)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Y in each set of Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], errors='ignore')
    filtered_data = data[data['Series'].isin(['I', 'II'])]
    sns.boxplot(x='Series', y='Y', data=filtered_data)
    plt.title("What is the difference in the distribution of Y between set I and set II of Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
